  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "The SS, he went away, but the Jewish doctor-- then he took off the thing, and then he put some cream on it, some healing creams.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And then it's-- the slow healing process started.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "He put a heavy bandage on it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I couldn't walk yet.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "But with great difficulty, I could hop out to the toilet if I had to.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And the big event was, of course, that the rumor went around by the last week of September that there will be a big selection on the 1st of October, a big selection, which every three months happens in this camp, 20,000 people.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And they will pull out the weakest 2,000 or 3,000, send them over to the gas chamber, and they-- they replenish the stock with fresh new arrivals, healthy, strong men.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they had to find out which are the-- those people who are no-- not really much useful for work-- for work in the coal mines or carrying bags of cement or so forth.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, I certainly wasn't fit to carry bags of cement.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I couldn't hardly go out to the toilet.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they came.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we heard the news, because the first day they checked all the regular blocks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "People had to run around 600 meters, and the-- the ones who couldn't run fast enough at-- at making a-- a full oval, then they were popped out, and then they were put on the list-- gas chamber-- and gas, you know.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the same night-- they didn't come to the hospital-- they were the-- the same night, one of my best friends-- a 36-year-old man, a factory owner in Budapest-- he came over to me to the hospital block-- to the-- to my block, and he said, imagine, they took-- put me on the list.",
      "word_count": 54
    }
  ],
